&lt;h1 id="see-randomness"&gt;See Randomness&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;April 2006, rev August 2009&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plato quotes Socrates as saying &amp;ldquo;the unexamined life is not worth living.&amp;rdquo; Part of what he meant was that the proper role of humans is to think, just as the proper role of anteaters is to poke their noses into anthills.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>